This paper deals with the analysis of error probability in communication channels, specifically the additive white Gaussian noise channel. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and its subfield of information theory and probability (cs.ITP). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which could place it under the categories of mathematical modeling (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with communication networks and their performance, which could place it under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
